## Version Control / Checkin Rules

- When committing, ALWAYS run `git status` to capture ALL modified, added, and deleted files before committing
- Never assume only newly added files need staging. Verify the commit list includes all changed files
- When user says to commit ONLY specific files, do NOT commit other files. Respect explicit scope constraints
- After commit, run `git status` again to verify nothing was missed
- Use `/checkin` and `/vcs-status` commands for VCS operations

## No Tick/Polling Rule

- Tick, Timer, polling are prohibited. Use event-driven patterns (delegates, callbacks, message handlers)
- Exception: Physics simulation, animation interpolation where Tick is unavoidable
- See `.claude/rules/coding/no-tick-polling.md` for details

